flowchart TD
    Start(["OneDrive.exe launched"]):::host
    Start --> Need["Process needs<br/>version.dll<br/>(static or LoadLibrary)"]:::need
    Need --> Loader["Windows loader runs<br/>Safe DLL Search Mode<br/>(default since XP SP2)"]:::loader

    Loader --> Step1{{"Step 1<br/>Application directory<br/>%LOCALAPPDATA%\Microsoft\OneDrive\"}}:::step1
    Step1 -- "version.dll FOUND<br/>(planted by attacker)" --> Hijack["MALICIOUS version.dll<br/>loaded into OneDrive.exe<br/>process address space"]:::hijack
    Step1 -. "if absent, continue" .-> Step2{{"Step 2<br/>System32<br/>C:\Windows\System32\"}}:::stepok
    Step2 -. "version.dll lives here<br/>(legitimate)" .-> Legit["LEGITIMATE version.dll<br/>(Microsoft signed)<br/>loaded normally"]:::legit
    Step2 -. "(hypothetical)" .-> Step3{{"Step 3<br/>16-bit system dir,<br/>then C:\Windows\,<br/>then PATH dirs"}}:::stepok
    Step3 -. "exhausted" .-> Fail(["DLL not found<br/>process fails to start"]):::fail

    Hijack --> DllMain["DllMain(DLL_PROCESS_ATTACH)<br/>DisableThreadLibraryCalls<br/>LoadLibraryA(self) - pin in memory"]:::dllmain
    DllMain --> Returns["DllMain returns TRUE<br/>OneDrive resumes startup"]:::dllmain
    Returns --> Call["OneDrive eventually calls<br/>VerQueryValueA / GetFileVersionInfoA / etc.<br/>during its update check"]:::host
    Call --> Stub["Malicious export stub:<br/>if (g_done) return 0;<br/>g_done = 1;<br/>DoWork();"]:::stub
    Stub --> Worker(["DoWork starts the<br/>full carrier chain<br/>(see kill chain diagram)"]):::worker

    %% Forwarding back to the real DLL keeps the host alive
    Stub -. "real Ver* calls<br/>not faked here -<br/>operator can add<br/>forwarders if host<br/>relies on the result" .-> Legit2["LEGITIMATE version.dll<br/>(loaded later by name<br/>from System32, or<br/>not at all if stub returns 0)"]:::legit

